method retrieves the pem encoded data from the stream and returns its decoded representation . method checks correctness of pem boundaries . it supposes that the first '- ' of the opening boundary has already been read from the stream . so first of all it checks that the leading bytes are equal to `` -- -- -begin '' boundary prefix . than if boundary_suffix is not null , it checks that next bytes equal to boundary_suffix + new line char [ s ] ( [ cr ] lf ) . if boundary_suffix parameter is null , method supposes free suffix format and skips any bytes until the new line. < br > after the opening boundary has been read and checked , the method read base64 encoded data until closing pem boundary is not reached. < br > than it checks closing boundary - it should start with new line + `` -- -- -end '' + boundary_suffix . if boundary_suffix is null , any characters are skipped until the new line. < br > after this any trailing new line characters are skipped from the stream , base64 encoding is decoded and returned .
